# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).

## [0.1.0] - 2024-03-08

### Added
- Initial release of Dictatux (forked from elograf)
- Multi-engine STT support: Whisper (Local), Vosk (Local), Google Cloud Speech, OpenAI Realtime API
- System tray icon with state visualization (loading, ready, dictating, suspended, stopped)
- Global keyboard shortcuts support (KDE via D-Bus)
- CLI interface for remote control (--begin, --end, --suspend, --resume, --toggle)
- Advanced configuration dialog with engine-specific settings
- Audio device selection (PulseAudio/parec)
- Pre/post command execution
- Multi-language support (i18n via Qt Linguist)
- Docker-based development tools for Qt resources and translations
- Comprehensive test suite with pytest

### Changed
- Project renamed from "elograf" to "Dictatux"
- Updated all branding and documentation
- Modular engine architecture with pluggable STT backends
- Migrated to PySide6

### Technical
- Abstract STT interface (STTController, STTProcessRunner)
- Engine lifecycle management with failure recovery
- Unified audio recorder with PyAudio/parec backends
- Qt resource compilation via Docker (no system Qt tools required)
